article.description: Sadler, Lundy lift Rider past Marist 69-59
article.headline: Sadler, Lundy lift Rider past Marist 69-59
article.linkText: Sadler, Lundy lift Rider past Marist 69-59
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Zedric Sadler scored 15 points, Xavier Lundy had 13 and Rider turned back Marist 69-59 on Friday. The Broncs (8-6, 2-1 Mid-Atlantic) made five of six free throws while forcing the Red Foxes (1-12, 0-3) into four misses and a turnover during the final minute. Philllip Lawrence hit a 3-pointer to pull Marist within 65-57 with 1:19 to play. The Red Foxes didn't score again until a Lawrence dunk as time ran out. Sadler scored at the halftime buzzer to tie the game at 29. Marist took a 48-45 lead midway through the second half when Shawn Valentine and Anthony D'Orazio made consecutive jumpers to put Rider up for good. That stretched to an 11-0 run, capped by Valentine's 3-pointer for a 57-48 lead with 5:40 to go. Chavaughn Lewis led Marist with 20 points, hitting four 3-pointers. The Foxes shot 42 percent, hitting 9 of 25 3s to stay close.
